 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zacatac>Zacatac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1665<br> <font color=#333333>(1/22/03 10:02:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=516.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question on training</span><hr size=1> Well the very first thing you need to do is go train 1 point in MEDITATE.  When you get new skills, they don't work until you activate them by training at least 1 point.  You will get other things like Dodge skill later that also needs to be trained.<br>
<br>
I spent many of mine on research skill, but you won't have to worry about that until after level 20.<br>
<br>
The specialization is another important one (also level 20).  Make sure you understand how it works when you get to that point.<br>
